A husband whose wife has just died of meningitis now faces an agonising wait to discover whether he too has contracted the disease.

George Cary, 65, was told that Lilian, his wife of 35 years, had contracted meningitis from tainted steroid injections intended to treat her back pain.

And Mr Cary's own back injections may have come from a contaminated batch too - meaning that when he laid his wife to rest today he still did not know if he too was suffering from the deadly illness.

