British-born Mrs Cary is one of 11 people across the U.S. to have died of fungal meningitis contracted from medication mixed by a pharmacy in Massachusetts.

Her husband went to an emergency room last weekend for a spinal tap, but the test results had not arrived by the time of Lilian's memorial service in Howell, Michigan on Tuesday.

'They advised me to watch for symptoms,' Mr Cary said. 'At this point, there's nothing abnormal, but they said the same thing when Lilian had hers.

'Not only have I lost my wife, but I'm watching the clock to see if anything develops.'

